o is that its designed to allow for short duration play sessions. problem is, at the current time, the only activity that fit such a short session are missions. will there be other viable alternative to get reasonable exp when we have only a couple hours to play ? <BR>gaute - n <BR>gaute - eh <BR>gaute - First of all, there will be a lot of roaming monsters, tiny camps and areas to explore in Shadowlands. Secondly, there will be hundreds (!) of mission dungeons, that will also instansiate (additional dungeons will be spawn if the previous one was too crowded). These <BR>gaute - there <BR>gaute - will contain bosses, chests, everything you know from a missions (except the reward). You can log out outside the dungeon, and stay there as long as you want! (No need to go back for an additional mission, like today). I dont think Shadowlands will be less friendly for solo players or shorter duration play sessions. It will simply be better for teams and large groups (20+)... <BR>gaute - I dont think Shadowlands will be less friendly for solo players or shorter duration play sessions. It will simply be better for teams and large groups (20+)... <BR>gaute - repost - sorry <BR><BR>Adrazar - Jerrikk: will there be shops in the shadowlands, and if so, any new kinds? <BR>Adrazar - Yes, there will be shops and yes, they will be different. But in most places they will be few and far apart. <BR>Adrazar - The Redeemed and Unredeemed sides will provide travellers with some basic shops, but the most interesting marketplaces are in the Yuttos settlements. There one can get hold of various instruments and raw materials that are otherwise hard to find. <BR><BR>blackmane - Schop: you stated that agents will have the highest damage per minute. where does this leave mas, being that the 2 ma advantages (highest damage over time, and best evades) are nowhere near met? <BR>blackmane - As I said with the agent question, MAs using their fists will be at, or around, the same level as the agent in 