 damage-dealing professions, or at least those at the top. <BR><BR>JimSalabim - Chronita: the knife or sharp object throwing skill is currently useless in ao - what kind (if any) implimentation will we see for it in sl? <BR>JimSalabim - It should be possible to find some use for it, but I'm not certain what we've agreed on there - I'd have to check on it. It is probably among the last minute priorities if it's there... <BR>JimSalabim - Sorry I can't be more spesific :/ <BR><BR>blackmane - Fixere: as the grid armor is going away in sl, will there be any other options for non-armor fixers rather than normal armor? <BR>blackmane - To put it simply, no. You will need to be wearing armor, like everyone else. <BR><BR>Marius - Hannobal: will players get manuals of perk lines or do we have to guess in which line to invest? <BR>Marius - marius: There will be help texts associated with the perks =) <BR><BR>gaute - Karrd: will there be a way to select which gs you zone into, or more specificly will there be an automated zone into the gs your team is in fuction? (ie: if someone dies in your team at to3w, everyone has to runout and reenter) <BR>gaute - We are working on the team-zoning thing, yes.It has high priority, but it is a technically challenging thing as it requires lot of intra-server-communication, so I am not 100% certain it will make it in. <BR>gaute - I think it is better to say, "im not sure" than to disappoint you all if it doesnt make it. You cant expect all of them to make it, but you should not expect none of them to make it either. <img src="i/expressions/face-icon-small-wink.gif" border="0"> <BR><BR>JimSalabim - Viro: will there be weapon sheathing in the possible future? or something where you can still have your weapon equipped but you can hold drinks & such at the same time? heh <BR>JimSalabim - It's indeed a nice feature, but it won't be part of the Shadowlands I'm afraid. Maybe in the next expansion - it would fit with the theme there. <BR><BR>Marius - Twicer: marius: will there be perks for tradeskills? <BR>Marius - marius: Engineer and Trader gets some perks that will help with their tradeskill process. <BR><BR>blackmane - Blasterx: what kind of new things the adv get, being that our top morph is practicly useless, what will we see in new morphs in sl? <BR>blackmane - There will be new, much nicer, versions of the wolf, sabretooth, and pit lizards coming. <BR>blackmane - Additionally, there will be an all-new polymoph that will enhance the healing abilities of the adventurer under certain circumstances. <BR>blackmane - One of the perk lines for the adventurer enables some new special attacks that can only be used in the polymorphed form (an example is the Devour attack which is a lifetap that can only be used when you are a wolf). <BR>blackmane - There are also rumors of a possible shadowy-enhancement to the leet line, but, shhhh on that <img src="i/expressions/face-icon-small-smile.gif" border="0"> <BR><BR>gaute - iged: in regards to faction standing , what benifits will it provide and what are some examples of how it is gained ? <BR>gaute - The faction standing is easily summed up as a gameplay mechanism for the Non Player Characters and Monsters in the game to decide HOW to react to you. They include: <BR>gaute - ) should I attack on long range (superaggro), b) should I attack on normal range (aggro), c) should I aid a friend being attacked, d) should I laugh at your death ;p, e) should I ignore you, f) should I trade with you and g) should I give you a "quest" or "static mission". <BR>gaute - e future? or something where you can still have your weapon equipped but you <BR>gaute - You shall be able to see by examining the NPC its standing with you. <BR>gaute - There is also a new Faction GUI... <BR><BR>blackmane - Twicer: adrazar: the keeper in shadowlands are supposed to be a tank-class although not as good at it as the enforcer, what makes the keeper unique (as opposed to just being a slightly toned down enf)? <BR>blackmane - The Keeper is a team-augmenting profession. Yes, they can be a tank if needed, but won't be as good as an enforcer or soldier. Yes, they do inflict good damage, but not at the top. <BR>blackmane - But the Keeper can have up to 3 different auras running at once, so they will be a benefit to any team with them. <BR>blackmane - The Keeper is based heavily on augmenting teams with their presence, not being a super tank. <BR><BR>JimSalabim - Triffid: qt: will the doc prof have any new items/nanos in sl. their ability and role have been static for a long time now <BR>JimSalabim - Yes, the Doctor will get armors, nanos and weapons in the Shadowlands - like other professions. Her role will still be that of the major healer - not sure what other direction you'd think it natural that she'd take... <img src="i/expressions/face-icon-small-smile.gif" border="0"> <BR><BR>blackmane - Doctors will be getting a third DoT line in SL. New DoTs will become available, much better than before, so the doctor won't be a healer and nothing else type of profession. <BR><BR>Adrazar - breezer: when i started playing anarchy online, one of the things i liked the most was that noone really knew what the world looked like and there were new discoveries made every day, that has changed alot since launch and today with most players knowing exact spawntimes of most uniques and even the content of the next patch the exploration part has dissapeared almost entirely. do you plan to bring any of this more back to life in shadowlands? <BR>Adrazar - Exploration has been one of the keywords throughout the making of the Shadowlands. <BR>Adrazar - Some very basic things contribute to making exploration a larger element of the playing experience, like for example that you can not fly in there, maps need to be put together and made before they are uploaded, resources can be found and items foraged in obscure parts of the world, monsters will have more varied behavior and at the same time can be manipulated in more ways than today. <BR>Adrazar - But the biggest "thing" here is that static content will be so much more abundant than it is today and even though it is static, it is not necessarily always predictable. <BR>Adrazar - All in all: The one who keeps his eyes open and wits about him on his journey through the Shadowlands, he will succeed better than others. And leave no stone unturned, you never know if there will be something that saves your skin in your next encounter. <BR><BR>gaute - Nexxium: will there be lvl caps to attack mobs on rk? or will lvl 220s be able take it all <BR>gaute - There will most likely be 1 or both of the following systems in place: 1. A "teleport away" system for high level characters in the area on the monsters hate-list. 2. A "level-restricted" loot code. <BR>gaute - It means that for SOME boss monsters, for some of their loot, it will disappear if the player did not receive experience for it. <BR>gaute - The alternative will be that lower level characters will never be able to gain "their own" treasure, as most normal monsters will be "walks in the park" for the highest levels. It is yet to be determined to which degree we put this in place... <BR><BR>Marius - Hannobal: when i asked about perk manuals i did mean that ie. when taking 1st perk of line, do players get to know what will be the last perk in that line? <BR>Marius - marius: oohh, sorry, misunderstood you =) Yes! you will be able to see all info related to the perks you can at some time use. <BR><BR>gaute - Lheann: with respect to title caps. we have heard that the skill budget is getting changed. will the title cap levels of today be gone when sl comes? <BR>gaute - No, that is not true. But! You will gain additional skill from perks as well. This will mean that your skill (disregarding new items or nanos) will be higher than today. The title cap ABOVE level 200 will be substansially higher, for both skills and abiliteis. I was refering to below 200 characters. <BR><BR>blackmane - Chronita: are there any plans to augment or add to the ma healing lines in sl? <BR>blackmane - Not directly. But the Disharmony perk line provides the MA with a permanent, innate lifetap that will affect the MA's attacks. <BR>blackmane - So the lifetap will help the MA heal himself, but the MA won't become a better healer of others, no. <BR><BR>Adrazar - MORB: dungeons all over the place sounds nice, but wont it draw interest too much away from outdoor areas, that are usually more varied and pleasing visually, like it is currently ? <BR>Adrazar - No, not really. The dungeons in the Shadowlands have a specific mission and there you can get hold of specific items and resources. But most of what yo NEED to do, hapens in the outdoor playfields, there is no way around that. <BR><BR>gaute - Mattie: its quite obvious that the game can not handle more than 40 or so people in the same area at once, as evidence in the tramendous lag at tower battles. how will this problem be fixed in shadowlands when so many people try and explore everything new? <BR>gaute - First of all, I think that if you have problems with around 40 people on your screen, please refer to technical FAQ's on how to reduce the rendering settings on your machine. <BR>gaute - Secondly, yes, there will be problems at the very outset, I am quite sure - and we expect it and are working with several methods to reduce the impact!! <BR>gaute - Still, our servers actually handle more than 60% more people in one area than one year ago, and more than 100% more people in one area than at launch. <BR><BR>JimSalabim - Berk: has there been any consideration in increasing the amount of variety in armor designs for higher end equipment? right now a large amount of armor available in the game at the high end is just a recolor or recycle of lower level armors. <BR>JimSalabim - Question Header <BR><BR>gaute - There will be several entrance points to the Shadowlands, spread over many playfields. You can get into it at 4-5 different places. We shall also add more, to spread people out, if necessary. <BR><BR>JimSalabim - We would like some variation between top and bottom level.. there will be some, but our resources are limited... and much work has gone into the profession spesific suits... I hope it will be enough to satisfy you... <BR><BR>gaute - eh, sorry <img src="i/expressions/face-icon-small-wink.gif" border="0"> <BR><BR>danielp - Zane0: any consideration of another ipr, or a quest to get more ipr points? <BR>danielp - There will to my knowledge not be any ip reset points offered within the Shadowlands expansion. <BR><BR>blackmane - Tyborg: when enforcers isent on the top of the damage dealing ladder, will they get any new way of taunting? <BR>blackmane - Yes. The Enforcer will get a lot of new ways to taunt. <BR>blackmane - There will be improved single-target taunts (up to 10k taunt per cast). <BR>blackmane - There will be perk special abilities for taunting. <BR>blackmane - There will be a taunt proc buff. <BR>blackmane - So, the enforcer will be able to deal out a huge amount of taunt to get and maintain aggro, never fear. <BR><BR>Adrazar - Lheann: concerning shops. with sl will we see items above ql125 available in shops on the rk side? <BR>Adrazar - As it is, only some selected shops in the Shadowlands carry items over level 125. <BR>Wolfgang - I would like to thank everyone for attending tonights Anarchy Online House of Commons Chat. The logs of the chat will be found over at http://ao.stratics.com later tonight. <BR>Wolfgang - Thanks again all! <BR><BR>gaute - Ok, thank you very much for turning up. Hope you had a good time, I did. Cya all in the Shadow <BR><BR>JimSalabim - Lands <BR>* Marius waves * <BR><BR>gaute - Shadow <BR><BR>Belith - box <BR><BR> 
